cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with performance optimization in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a mathematical coverage model and a sparse-domain based recovery method, both of which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The proposed network clustering mechanism and routing protocol involve collaboration among nodes, which is a characteristic of social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper mentions an improved computation complexity for the proposed routing protocol, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed averaging filter for recovering corrupted data samples can be considered as a multimedia processing technique.
